Explanation:
- All six entries correspond directly to router.<method>(path, handler) calls in routes/invoices.js. The paths are taken from literal strings in that file; Express-style path parameters (":id") have been converted to the required "{id}" form.
- The handlers (getTotalCount, getInvoice, getInvoicesByUser, createInvoice, updateInvoice, deleteInvoice) are imported from ../controllers/invoices.js, so their implementations are not present in this file (implementationPresent: false).
- None of the paths in this file are declared as prefixes (they are specific route patterns on the router). Paths are not derived from any convention in the file â€” they are explicit literals.
- These routes implement typical RESTful invoice operations (list, get by id, create, update, delete, plus a count endpoint), so isRest is true. There is no indication they are for testing, so isTest is false.
